Privacy Policy
	1. General Information
		This Privacy Policy explains how personal data is collected, used, and protected in connection with the project [Project Name].
		By using the project or providing any personal data, you agree to this Privacy Policy.
	2. Data Controller
		The data controller is the owner of the project [Shadows Of Hytale], operating under the pseudonym [NecroDev].
		For any privacy-related inquiries, you may contact the Project Owner via email at [contactnecrodev@gmail.com] or via Discord [my username: KryPla]
		Please note:
		• The Project Owner uses a pseudonym publicly and does not disclose their legal name for personal privacy reasons.
		• This may include situations such as name changes, transition processes, or other personal considerations.
		• All personal data is still processed in full compliance with applicable privacy laws.
	3. Data We Collect
		Depending on how you interact with the project, we may collect the following data:
		• username or display name,
		• email address (if provided voluntarily),
		• payment-related identifiers provided by third-party payment processors (we do not store full payment details),
		• technical data such as IP address, browser type, device information, or basic usage data (if applicable).
	4. Payments
		All payments are processed by third-party payment providers (e.g. PayPal, Stripe, or similar).
		• We do not collect or store credit card numbers or full payment details.
		• Payment providers process personal data according to their own privacy policies.
	5. Purpose of Data Processing
		Personal data is processed solely for the following purposes:
		• operating and maintaining the project,
		• granting or managing the Supporter Pass (if applicable),
		• communicating with users regarding the project,
		• improving the project and user experience,
		• complying with legal obligations, if required.
	6. Cookies and Similar Technologies
		1. The project may use cookies or similar technologies to ensure proper functionality and improve user experience.
		2. Cookies may include:
			• essential cookies required for basic operation,
			• functional or analytical cookies (if applicable).
		3. Users may disable cookies in their browser settings.
		Please note that disabling cookies may affect certain functionalities of the project.
	7. Data Sharing
		Personal data is not sold, rented, or shared with third parties, except:
		• payment processors (for handling payments),
		• service providers necessary for operating the project,
		• when required by law or legal authorities.
	8. Data Retention
		Personal data is stored only for as long as necessary to fulfill the purposes described in this Privacy Policy, or as required by applicable law.
		Data may be deleted or anonymized once it is no longer needed.
	9. User Rights (GDPR / EEA)
		If you are located in the European Economic Area (EEA), you have certain rights under the General Data Protection Regulation (GDPR), including:
		• the right to access your personal data,
		• the right to request correction or deletion of your data,
		• the right to restrict or object to processing,
		• the right to data portability,
		• the right to withdraw consent at any time (where processing is based on consent).
		To exercise these rights, you may contact the Project Owner using the contact details provided above.
	10. Legal Basis for Processing (GDPR)
		Personal data is processed on one or more of the following legal bases:
		• the user’s consent,
		• the necessity to perform or manage project-related interactions,
		• compliance with legal obligations,
		• the legitimate interests of the Project Owner, where applicable.
	11. Data Security
		Reasonable technical and organizational measures are taken to protect personal data.
		However, no method of transmission or storage can be guaranteed to be 100% secure.
	12. Children’s Privacy
		The project is not intended for individuals under the age required by applicable law.
		No personal data is knowingly collected from children.
	13. Changes to This Privacy Policy
		This Privacy Policy may be updated at any time.
		The current version will be made available by the Project Owner.
	14. Final Provisions
		If any part of this Privacy Policy is found to be invalid, the remaining provisions shall remain in effect.
